Fifty four out of 100 pupils in standard three cannot do class two work in Nyandarua county, and five out of 100 in standard eight cannot do class two work, a report by Uwezo Kenya indicates.The findings released at Aberdare Resort, Ol Kalou, on Friday indicate Nyandarua North&rsquo;s academic performance is better than Nyandarua South&rsquo;s. The study was conducted in Nyandarua between September and October 2015. During the assessment, 617 households were visited, and 1,210 children assessed on basic literacy and numeracy skills using the standard two syllabus.Sixty schools in the county were surveyed.